The paper focuses on the application of QuickProp for training deep neural networks in computer vision tasks, specifically semantic segmentation. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also evaluates the performance of QuickProp compared to gradient descent, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the optimization of neural networks, which is a subfield of computational neuroscience (cs.NE) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) tasks such as semantic segmentation, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL).
